{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 139,
      "text": "The survivors of concentration camps did not rate any better or different from anybody else.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 140,
      "text": "And we had to compete for jobs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 141,
      "text": "In fact, i couldn't find a job, because to work in a factory that was making radios, you had to be a citizen.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I couldn't find a job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eventually I found a job as, of all the things in the world, in a place that was doing enamel work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And lo and behold, in the United States, in Paterson, New Jersey, I was back in front of an oven, generating 1,000 degrees of heat when the door was opened.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I realized that this is the worse of the two evils, and maybe I should go back and look if I can't go to the trade of carpentry, which I had some exposure to.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had some carpentry and cabinet making experience.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I gravitated into that, and I began to work in a furniture shop in Paterson, New Jersey.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I got full employment at that time, and received, in 1949-- when I began working in Paterson New Jersey, I worked for an outfit by the name of-- well, Gordon Brothers was the second employer.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was another one whose name I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was the furniture making business, and my wages were $0.75 an hour.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember my cousin with whom I lived at the time asking me, well, are you now a happy man earning $0.75 an hour?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, yes, I'm extremely happy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm doing extremely well.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He says, well, how much money would you need to make to be really happy-like?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, if I ever made $50 a week, I would be the happiest man alive.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
